tool.name: qiime2 phylogeny iqtree
tool.description: Construct a phylogenetic tree with IQ-TREE.

param.name: alignment
param.label: alignment: FeatureData[AlignedSequence]
param.help: [required] Aligned sequences to be used for phylogenetic reconstruction.

param.name: seed
param.label: seed: Int
param.help: [optional] Random number seed. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: __q2galaxy__GUI__select__
param.label: n_cores: Int % Range(1, None) | Str % Choices('auto')
param.help: [default: 1] The number of cores to use for parallel processing. Use `auto` to let IQ-TREE automatically determine the optimal number of cores to use.

param.name: n_cores
param.label: n_cores: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [default: 1] The number of cores to use for parallel processing. Use `auto` to let IQ-TREE automatically determine the optimal number of cores to use.

param.name: n_cores_max
param.label: n_cores_max: Int % Range(2, None)
param.help: [optional] Limits the maximum number of cores to be used when 'n_cores' is set to 'auto'.

param.name: n_runs
param.label: n_runs: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [default: 1] Number of indepedent runs. Multiple independent runs (e.g. 10) can outperform a single run in terms of likelihood maximisation.

param.name: substitution_model
param.help: [default: 'MFP'] Model of Nucleotide Substitution. If not provided, IQ-TREE will determine the best fit substitution model automatically.

param.name: n_init_pars_trees
param.label: n_init_pars_trees: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [optional] Number of initial parsimony trees. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: n_top_init_trees
param.label: n_top_init_trees: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [optional] Number of top initial trees. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: n_best_retain_trees
param.label: n_best_retain_trees: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [optional] Number of best trees retained during search. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: n_iter
param.label: n_iter: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [optional] Fix number of iterations to stop. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: stop_iter
param.label: stop_iter: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [optional] Number of unsuccessful iterations to stop. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: perturb_nni_strength
param.label: perturb_nni_strength: Float % Range(0.01, 1.0)
param.help: [optional] Perturbation strength for randomized NNI. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: spr_radius
param.label: spr_radius: Int % Range(1, None)
param.help: [optional] Radius for parsimony SPR search. If not set, program defaults will be used. See IQ-TREE manual for details.

param.name: allnni
param.label: allnni: Bool
param.help: [default: No] Perform more thorough NNI search.

param.name: fast
param.label: fast: Bool
param.help: [default: No] Fast search to resemble FastTree.

param.name: alrt
param.label: alrt: Int % Range(1000, None)
param.help: [optional] Single branch test method. Number of bootstrap replicates to perform an SH-like approximate likelihood ratio test (SH-aLRT). Minimum of 1000 replicates is recomended. Can be used with other 'single branch test methods'. Values reported in the order of: alrt, lbp, abayes.

param.name: abayes
param.label: abayes: Bool
param.help: [default: No] Single branch test method. Approximate Bayes test. Can be used with other 'single branch test methods'. Values reported in the order of: alrt, lbp, abayes.

param.name: lbp
param.label: lbp: Int % Range(1000, None)
param.help: [optional] Single branch test method. Number of bootstrap replicates to perform a fast local bootstrap probability method. Minimum of 1000 replicates is recomended. Can be used with other 'single branch test methods'. Values reported in the order of: alrt, lbp, abayes.

param.name: safe
param.label: safe: Bool
param.help: [default: No] Safe likelihood kernel to avoid numerical underflow.

tool.help:
QIIME 2: phylogeny iqtree ========================= Construct a phylogenetic tree with IQ-TREE.
Outputs: -------- :tree.qza: The resulting phylogenetic tree.
|
Description: ------------ Construct a phylogenetic tree using IQ-TREE (http://www.iqtree.org/) with automatic model selection.
|
